      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The fear that exceptions erode the rule of law is a significant concern in democratic discourse. If exemptions become too broad, they risk allowing private moral systems to dictate public governance, weakening the secular foundation. Ultimately, compelling uniformity requires a strong legal framework that clearly delineates when a sincerely held belief constitutes a legitimate claim, and when it becomes a refusal to adhere to universally applied civic duties.",
